Paramedics say they found the man surrounded by 20 to 30 people on the corner of West and Church streets just after midnight. JOHANNESBURG - A man believed to be in his 30s has been found dead in Pietermaritzburg after being stabbed in the chest.Paramedics say they found the man surrounded by 20 to 30 people on the corner of West and Church streets just after midnight.Officials say it's not yet clear how the man was killed.ER24's Annine Siddal says: ER24 paramedics arrived to a hostile scene and found the man at the side of the road. There was nothing ER24 could do to save the man and he was declared dead on scene. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)